observations.recommendation:
6.17 We recommended and the LCE agreed to:
a. Instruct the Municipal Accountant to properly accrue and transfer the unexpended 5% LDRRMF from the General Fund to the Trust Fund account;
b. Instruct the Municipal Accountant to draw a JEV to reclassify the entry made for the acquired equipment for the LDRRM;
c. Require the Administrative Officer (HRMO II):
1. To review the designation order for LDRRMO II if in accordance with the existing CSC rules and regulation;
2. Expedite the recruitment process for LDRRMO II; and
3. Review the plantilla positions and initiate the creation or establishment of three (3) DRRM staff;

6.18 The MA commented that she has transferred the unexpended LDRRMF from General Fund to Special Trust Fund. The MA also recognized the adjusting entry to for the PPEs. The HRMO II also agreed and will expedite the process on the recruitment of LDRRMO II. Likewise, the management will look into the fund availability if additional three (3) DRRM staff can be accommodated taking into account the Personnel Services limitations.

7.17 We recommended and the LCE agreed to;
1. Direct the Municipal General Services Officer to establish control in monitoring Purchase Orders or contract with pending delivery of goods or services;
2. Direct the Municipal Accountant to:
a) Draw a JEV for the recovery of the liquidated damages from supplier and send demand letter for the refund;
b) Draw a JEV to recognize a receivable from the Job Order Personnel and offset/deduct the collectibles from their respective salaries and return the amount of ₱50,500.00 to DOLE-8 once collected; and
c) Draw a JEV for the unrecorded refund to DOH-8 of ₱23,409.01.
3. Direct the Municipal PESO Manager Designate that henceforth, to revalidate list of beneficiaries of the same programs to make sure that there will be no duplication of benefits;
4. Require the PHWs concerned to submit immediately to the audit team, thru the Accountant, the following documents to establish their claim to SRAs under AO No. 36:
a) Authority for the entitlement of the allowance/ office order/ authority to report for work;
b) Daily Time Records with Biometric printouts/copies of logbook or Certificate of Attendance in the COVID Facility/Center by their immediate supervisor during the period of claims;
c) Accomplishment reports indicating the number of COVID patients attended to in a day; and
d) For health workers not directly catering COVID-19 patients, an explanation as to the scientific basis for the premise that healthcare workers not directly catering to COVID-19 patients are equally exposed to COVID-19 and can be considered “in contact with COVID-19 patients”, and thus should be given the SRA.

7.18 The MGSO will have to establish a monitoring tool for the pending Purchase Orders and Contracts. Likewise, the Designated PESO Manager reassured to revalidate list of beneficiaries for similar activities. Meanwhile, the Municipal Accountant has prepared the correcting entries in the books of accounts. Moreover, the Management agreed to recover the payment made to ineligible TUPAD beneficiaries and refund to DOLE-8.

We recommended that the LCE requires the Municipal Accountant to:
a. draw a Journal Entry Voucher to adjust the understatement of the outstanding SDO, and include in the schedule the P182,352.96, as basis in the composition of the outstanding cash advances to the outstanding SDO, and provide the composition of the outstanding cash advances to date;
b. include in the Schedule of Unliquidated Cash Advances the outstanding cash advances totaling P182,352.96, as basis in the issuance of demand letters to accountable officers with unliquidated cash advances to date;
c. recommend the suspension of the salaries of accountable officers who continuously fail to submit their liquidation reports;
d. stop the grant of additional cash advances to employees with previous unliquidated cash advances; and
e. exert more effort to identify the remaining unaccounted cash advances totaling P826,577.05, and immediately apply appropriate actions to settle the same.

We recommended that the LCE requires:

1. The Municipal Accountant to:

a. Reconcile monthly the amount withheld from payroll/DVs on premium contributions against the remittance list;

b. Prepare necessary journal entries to adjust year-end balances and submit the lacking Official Receipt;

2. The Municipal Treasurer to remit the withheld funds on time and intact;

3. Henceforth, the Municipal Accountant and Treasurer to strictly adhere to the provisions cited in PD No. 1445, PhilHealth Circular No. 01-2014, and IRR of R.A. 7875 on the remittance of premiums and contributions withheld. This is without prejudice to the issuance of notice of disallowance on the penalties totaling P1,071.27 which was paid out of LGU fund.
